cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.MM, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the construction of a schedule for multi-hop packet radio networks, which falls under the domain of networking. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of deterministic and random backoffs to avoid collisions, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The protocol proposed in the paper is distributive in nature, which falls under the domain of distributed computing. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of short acknowledgement control packets and link layer delayed acknowledgements, which are related to multimedia communication. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper assesses the performance of the proposed protocol through simulation, which is related to systems and control.
